y_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing URLClassLoader in Native Image**\\n\\nI'm exploring whether Native Image supports URLClassLoader for resource handling. I think I can create a temporary directory for paths, with userJar pointing to gwt-user.jar or any valid path. If I pass a temp directory containing the module's XML, getResource should return a valid URL without relying on the current classpath. It seems like Native Image could handle URLClassLoader for filesystem resources, which is encouraging. If it works, I may have tests validate both found and missing resources for robustness.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Utilizing @TempDir for Testing**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how to avoid relying on external resources by using @TempDir to create a path for CreatorUtilitiesCoverage.gwt.xml. Then, I could use validatePathsAndModules with \\\"gwt-user.jar\\\" while passing in the temp directory and a list containing the module name \\\"org_gwtproject.gwt_user.creator.CreatorUtilitiesCoverage.\\\" This approach seems straightforward, allowing me to ensure the test runs smoothly without needing to pull in source resources directly. I'll see how this plays out in practice!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_XI1ZeZYSY4JCJFIYnCMl4dRm|fc_08e5f8857f9b76150169f59335b2ac81a08f98f463c7f70eff", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/org.gwtproject/gwt-user -path '*2.11.0*' -type f | head -20 && for j in $(find ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/org.gwtproject/gwt-user -path '*2.11.0*' -name '*.jar' | head -5); do echo $j; jar tf \"$j\" | grep '\\.gwt\\.xml$' | head -20; done", "timeout": 20}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 309, "output": 1023, "cacheRead": 19968, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 21300, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777701671981, "responseId": "resp_08e5f8857f9b761